Add IoT keystore shared libraries

Add libraries and headers for IoT keystore. Since libraries are
shared, allow possibility that symbolic links have to be copied
along with library file. Extend that feature to static libraries.

Resolves: LE-16058
Change-Id: I55ba0985c0865071bec65a104af8d35acac236c7
Signed-off-by: Zoran Markovic <zmarkovic@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Add IoT keystore shared libraries

comments.message: This change adds IoT keystore shared libraries to proprietary/qct layer. Looks like build issues were resolved.

Different behaviour from previous simple copy from name -> name, single file.
Probably worth commenting the intention a bit more explicitly - iterate over files existing in a directory and copy them all, under $DEST/lib. 
Also worth commenting on why now symlinks are no longer de-referenced (-P)
